cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper discusses techniques for simulation and prediction with Gaussian process (GP) dynamics, which are commonly used in machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses safety-critical applications, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of GP dynamics and trajectory prediction suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
